properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 2:50PM CST until January 11 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Winter Storm This Afternoon into Late Saturday...

.A large low pressure system will affect Iowa to end the week
spreading two episodes of wintry precipitation across the state.
The first push will bring snow and blowing snow through central
sections with freezing rain and a wintry mix south this
lasting into at least the evening hours. The second push Saturday
will mainly be snow and blowing snow, ending from west to east
during the evening hours. Moderate to heavy snow storm total
accumulations are expected over the southeast two-thirds of Iowa
by the time the storm ends Saturday evening.

* WHAT...Moderate snow expected. Total snow accumulations 3 to 5
inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph later today.

* WHERE...Portions of central Iowa.

* WHEN...From 3 PM this afternoon to 6 AM CST Saturday. Majority
of snow will occur this afternoon and evening, with some more
light snow possible Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions, especially during
periods of snowfall. Areas of blowing snow could significantly
reduce visibility. The hazardous conditions will likely impact
the Friday evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST SATURDAY
